{"questionId":"22630871","questionHtml":"<p>Write down an integral that can be used to find the area of the shaded region.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>4</mn></msubsup><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>4</mn></msubsup><mi>h</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for a correct integral, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct limits in the correct location.</p>\n<p>Award at most <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em> if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math> is omitted.</p>\n<p>Award at most <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em> for \"integral <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>\" or integral <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>, this is not the correct integrand.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22630871","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.5ci","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down an integral that can be used to find the area of the shaded region.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}